paragraph:
Shoaib Makani is known for their contribution as CEO at KeepTruckin. KeepTruckin co-founder and CEO, Shoaib has extensive experience in entrepreneurship and venture capital. He leverages this experience to guide our overall business strategy. Prior to founding KeepTruckin, Shoaib worked at Khosla Venture, where he led investments in consumer and enterprise technology companies including [Instacart](/org/instacart), [Everlane](/org/everlane), Yammer, and [HackerRank](/org/hackerrank). Prior to joining [Khosla Ventures](/org/khosla-ventures), Shoaib led business development for Google’s mobile advertising business in Asia and Latin America. He holds a BSc in Economics from The London School of Economics. Education:  in 2000 - 2002 from Texas Academy of Mathematics and Science ( to ). Bachelor's (4 year program) in Government and Economics from London School of Economics and Political Science (LSE) (d2003-XX-XX to d2006-XX-XX).  in 2002 - 2004 from New York University (NYU) ( to ). Alex Buttle is known for their contribution as Vice President at Motorway. Alex Buttle is the Co-Founder & Marketing Director at [Motorway](/org/motorway). Previously, Alex was a Digital Marketing Consultant at [Student.com](/org/student-com). Alex holds a degree in Geography from the [University College London](/org/ucl). Education: Bachelor's (4 year program) in Geography from University College London (UCL) (d1996-XX-XX to d1999-XX-XX). High School or Equivalent in GCSEs, A-Levels from Sidmouth College (d1989-XX-XX to d1996-XX-XX). Bachelor's (4 year program) in  from BSc Geography, University College LondonGraduated 1999 ( to ). Career: Investor at Appear Here from d2012-12-01 to , where Angel investor / advisor.  Appear Here is an online marketplace to list, discover and book short-term retail space around the UK. Co-Founder & Marketing Director at Motorway from d2016-09-XX to , where Co-founder focusing on digital marketing, PPC, SEO, CRM, PR, content, display and radio/ TV advertising. And cars. Investor at Mention Me from d2015-04-XX to , where Angel investor. Mention Me enables businesses to supercharge their customer growth with referrals. Co-Founder, VP Growth at Motorway from d2016-09-01 to , where  Investor at Opendesk from d2014-06-XX to d2020-10-XX, where Investor / advisor. Designer furniture for your work space. OpenDesk is a global community of designers and makers. Digital Marketing Consultant / Strategic Advisor at Student.com from d2016-01-XX to d2016-08-XX, where Consulting and advising on PPC, digital marketing and online traffic growth globally. Student.com is the leading global marketplace for student housing. Digital Marketing Consultant at Various Startups from d2015-12-XX to d2016-08-XX, where Google, PPC, Facebook marketing and traffic growth/ conversion advisor at a number of start ups and established companies, including:

- Appear Here - the leading online marketplace for pop-up retail spaces
- Boomf - magical personalised marshmallows
- momondo/ Cheapflights - global travel brand comparing billions of flight and hotel deals
- Doctify - find the best doctors and health specialists near you
- OpenDesk - a marketplace for furniture designers and makers

- Simplify Digital - online comparison business (owned by Dixons Carphone)
- Voltz - the energy comparison genie in your pocket (owned by Dixons Carphone)
- Kindness.org - the nonprofit making it simple to choose kindness Investor at CoinDesk from d2013-01-XX to d2016-03-XX, where Angel investor. CoinDesk is the world leader in news and information on digital currencies. Founded by Shakil Khan, Coindesk was acquired by Digital Currency Group in 2016. Co-founder & CMO at Top10 from d2013-01-XX to d2016-01-XX, where Co-founder & CMO of Top10 - your hotel shortlist.

Responsible for all traffic acquisition:

- search (PPC & SEO)
- mobile app installs
- social media
- programmatic advertising
- display retargeting
- content strategies
- email marketing
- CRM 
- PR strategy 

Also launched a series of TV and outdoor ads.

Due to shifting market dynamics, the founding team wound down the company in late 2015. Marketing Director & Founder, uSwitch Communications at Uswitch from d2007-01-XX to d2013-06-XX, where Founder & marketing director of Top10 Broadband and Top10 Mobile Phones (which combined became uSwitch Communications Ltd on acquisition by uSwitch). 

Responsible for all aspects of uSwitch's traffic growth in the broadband and mobile space. 

Architected and grew a content, SEO, paid search and retargeting strategy with a £15m annual advertising spend with positive ROI. 

The acquisition of Top10 doubled uSwitch's existing revenue between 2010 and 2012. Co-founder & Marketing Director (Official Space) at officebroker from d2005-11-XX to d2011-12-XX, where UK's leading serviced office space comparison website driving upwards of 3,000+ commercial property leads per month. 

Official Space was acquired by OfficeBroker.com in 2010. paragraph: Harry Jones is known for their contribution as Founder at Motorway. Harry Jones is the Co-Founder & CPO at [Motorway](/org/motorway). Previously, Harry was the Founder & Chief Product Officer at Top10. Harry holds a degree in Graphic Design from Ravensbourne University London. Education: Bachelor's (4 year program) in Graphic Design from Ravensbourne (d2002-XX-XX to d2005-XX-XX). Foundation Diploma, Art + Design in Distinction from Weston College (d2001-XX-XX to d2002-XX-XX). Degree in Foundation Diploma, Art + Design from Weston College (d2001-XX-XX to d2002-XX-XX).  in  from The Blue School (d1996-XX-XX to d2001-XX-XX). Career: Co-Founder & CPO at Motorway from d2016-09-XX to , where Building the future of online car commerce. Founder & Chief Product Officer at Top10 from d2011-XX-XX to d2015-12-XX, where Top10 started life as a voting and recommendation platform built around top 10 lists. We launched at the LAUNCH Conference in 2011 and went on to raise over $12m from investors including Accel and Balderton.We developed innovative products for the web and were the first to build an app for Spotify’s native app platform. The business attracted hundreds of thousands of users around the globe who recommended millions of items from their favourite Apple products to Arnie films.In 2012 we pivoted into the travel space, developing Top10 Hotels. Working closely with Booking.com, Expedia, Priceline and dozens of other OTAs we launched an ambitious product offering comprehensive hotel recommendation, price comparison and booking all in one place. I headed up the product and engineering team, growing the company to a headcount of 25 talented designers and engineers. Notable achievements include winning the App Store 'App of the Year 2014' and 'Best New App' in 125+ territories for our iOS hotel booking app; and being a launch partner of Apple Pay in the UK. Co-Founder & CPO at Top10 from d2011-02-XX to d2015-12-XX, where  Non-Executive Director at Uswitch from d2011-06-XX to d2013-06-XX, where  Founder & Director at Uswitch from d2006-01-XX to d2011-06-XX, where Co-founded the UK's largest broadband and mobile phone comparison with over 1.5 million visitors per month.Disrupted the telecoms comparison industry through an unrivalled user experience, innovative online tools such as StreetStats and massive marketing scale.Acquired by uSwitch.com, 2011. Co-Founder & Director at Official Space from d2006-XX-XX to d2009-XX-XX, where Official Space is one of the most popular search engines for office space, connecting businesses with office space across the UK and the world. I headed up the design and technology arm of the business, developing both the consumer-facing experience and the back-end technology.Acquired August 2009. Co-Founder & Director at LifeCube & LoanCube from d2006-XX-XX to d2007-XX-XX, where Co-founded LifeCube and LoanCube, a set of consumer finance websites, generating secured loan, life insurance and medical insurance leads. The business grew quickly, delivering ours partners tens of thousands of leads per month. I headed up the design and technical teams, achieving industry-leading website conversion rates.Acquired by Lightstate Ltd., June 2007. Later acquired by buy.at and Aol. Designer & Developer at Freelance from d1999-XX-XX to d2006-XX-XX, where  Designer & Developer at Climate Impact Partners from d2002-XX-XX to d2004-XX-XX, where Responsible for designing and developing futureforests.com and online campaigns for clients such as Avis, Coldplay, The Sunday Times, The Body Shop and Scottish Power.Also designed & built the world's first online carbon calculator, enabling people to calculate their carbon footprint through a web app.  Skills include: supply chain management, software development, user centered design, internet marketing, development, advertising, management, economics, ui design, teaching, startup, html5, sales, ux, user experience design, product development, interaction design, email marketing, design strategy, graphic design, product design, user interface, typography, web design, marketing, CSS, User Interface Design, User-centered Design, Concept Development, Online Advertising, Web Development, User Experience, Start-ups, HTML 5, Priceline, Accel.

paragraph: Tom Leathes is known for their contribution as CEO at Motorway. Tom Leathes is the Co-Founder & CEO at [Motorway](/org/motorway). Previously, Tom was the Founder & CEO at Top10. Tom holds a degree in Geography from the [University College London](/org/ucl). Education: Geography in Geography from University College London (UCL) (d1998-XX-XX to d2001-XX-XX). Degree in Geography from University College London (UCL) (d1998-XX-XX to d2001-XX-XX). Geography, Geography in  from University College London (UCL) (d1998-XX-XX to d2001-XX-XX). Career: Founder & CEO at Motorway from d2016-07-16 to , where Motorway is the UK's fastest-growing used car marketplace. We connect people selling their car directly with our network of more than 4,000 verified car dealers, matching each seller with the dealer who most wants to buy their car. Motorway has grown to a team of over 400 people in London, Brighton and around the world, and we are growing fast. If you’d like to join us, check out our latest jobs and apply today: Angel Investor and Advisor at Various Startups - MAGNIFY Twimic FAQApp FTFun from d2012-01-XX to , where Angel investor / advisor in various startups including:- Appear Here - the leading online marketplace for pop-up retail spaces- CoinDesk - the largest content and data platform for bitcoin and other cryptocurrencies- OpenDesk - a marketplace for furniture designers and makers- Student.com - a global booking platform for student accommodation Founder & CEO at Top10 from d2011-07-XX to d2015-12-23, where A hotel recommendation app, Top10 instantly analysed millions of data points to find the best 10 hotels in any destination, always at the lowest price. We quickly became one of the fastest-growing travel startups in a highly competitive space. Top10 had class-leading apps and technology to simplify the experience of finding the perfect hotel. Launched in the UK and USA, built a very talented team of 30 and was awarded Apple's Best App of 2014. Raised $12.5m in VC funding from… Non-Executive Advisor at Uswitch from d2011-06-XX to d2013-06-XX, where  Founder & Director at Uswitch from d2006-07-XX to d2011-06-16, where Built the UK's biggest price comparison site for broadband, mobile phones and more. Without any external funding and starting with a team of three, we grew to a million users a month, Â£16m in annual revenues and an amazing team of 30 people. We built innovative technology solutions (such as StreetStats) and simple tools to compare and buy the best mobile and broadband deals on the market.Acquired by uSwitch.com in 2011 Founder & Director at officebroker from d2007-08-XX to d2009-10-XX, where OfficialSpace.co.uk is the UK’s favourite office space website, enabling small companies to compare 1,000s of available offices to let. Grew from scratch in under two years to be UK's biggest platform of it's kind, helping to find new offices for thousands of companies. Acquired by OfficeBroker.com in 2009 Founder & Director at AOL from d2006-06-XX to d2007-06-XX, where Built LoanCube.co.uk and LifeCube.co.uk (a suite of consumer finance services) into highly profitable lead-generation websites for secured loans and life insurance, generating huge amounts of new customers for some of the UK’s biggest lenders and insurers. Acquired by AOL in 2007 Founder & Director at Acre from d2003-09-XX to d2006-07-XX, where Co-founded Acre in 2003. Saw an open market niche for a high-quality recruitment firm focusing on the then emerging corporate responsibility, climate change and sustainability markets. Acre has grown to be the world leader in sustainability recruitment, with 45 staff and offices in London and New York. Acre was voted the UK's ‘Agency of the Year’ in the 2014 International Recruitment Awards. I moved to a Non-Exec role in 2006 and continue to advise Acre's board. Account Manager at Natural Capital Partners from d2001-09-XX to d2003-09-XX, where Natural Capital Partners (then Future Forests) is a first-mover in carbon and emissions solutions for individuals and companies, helping them to manage their climate change impacts. paragraph: Varun Singh is known for their contribution as Vice President at Moveworks. Varun Singh is a product manager at [Facebook](https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/facebook), an online social networking service.  Starting out as a researcher at UCLA and the Baylor College of Medicine, Singh went on to work as an engineer at Emcor Group before moving on to Sefaira as a senior vice president of product development.  Singh holds a bachelor’s degree in mechanical engineering from the Delhi College of Engineering, a master’s degree in mechanical engineering from the University of California, and a PhD in mechanical engineering from the University of Maryland College Park. Education: PhD or other Doctorate in Engineering and Design Optimization from University of Maryland (d2006-05-XX to d2009-01-XX). Master's (6 year program) in Engineering and Applied Mathematics from University of California Los Angeles (UCLA) (d2002-09-XX to d2004-01-XX). Bachelor's (4 year program) in Mechanical Engineering from Delhi College of Engineering (d1998-XX-XX to d2002-XX-XX).  in  from Delhi Public School - R. K. Puram (d1984-XX-XX to d1998-XX-XX). Career: Founder and Vice President, Product at Moveworks from d2016-XX-XX to , where Moveworks is revolutionizing how companies support their employees — with the first AI platform that delivers instant help at work™.The modern workday is full of disruptions, from IT issues to HR updates to policy changes. paragraph: Jiang Chen is known for their contribution as Ph.D. Yale University 1996. Jiang Chen is the Founder & VP Machine Learning at Moveworks. He is a former Software Engineer & Tech Lead at Airbnb and Staff Software Engineer at Google. Mr. Chen graduated from Tsinghua University with a bachelor's degree in Computer Science and received a Ph.D. in Computer Science at Yale University. Education: PhD or other Doctorate in Computer Science from Yale University (d2001-XX-XX to d2006-XX-XX). Bachelor's (4 year program) in Computer Science from Tsinghua University (d1997-XX-XX to d2001-XX-XX). Career: Founder & Vice President of Machine Learning at Moveworks from d2016-12-XX to , where I lead the Moveworks machine learning team building conversational AI that resolves employees' IT issues instantly and autonomously. Using the latest NLP and deep learning techniques, we've built an enterprise resolution platform that understands the user's intent, converses with the user to find the right resolution, and when possible resolves the user's issue immediately through its integration with backend IT systems. Our system learns quickly from small (by ML standards) datasets to understand employee requests in chat.Our team is growing fast and If you want to make an impact at a modern, AI-first company, working with cutting-edge technology and solving real problems, please reach out to me or check out our careers page. Founder & VP Machine Learning at Moveworks from d2016-12-XX to , where  Software Engineer & Tech Lead at Airbnb, Inc. from d2015-06-XX to d2016-11-XX, where Tech Lead for search ranking team, responsible for building machine learning models of search to booking process and implementing improvements to drive booking growth. Watch my Search at Airbnb tech talk: Staff Software Engineer at Google from d2009-12-XX to d2015-06-XX, where Part of the founding team who starts Google’s open domain question/answering project, composed of veteran and top NLP researchers with the goal of saving user’s reading time by directly presenting answers. Built a large scale machine learning service that automatically infers semantic meaning from webpages. This service was launched in the beginning of 2014 and now accounts for a large portion of all searches, including text (Google Search) and voice (Google Home). I was the tech lead for questions with short answers. For examples of my work, search in Google:-What car did james bond drive in skyfall-who was the us president who first brought pets into white house-Who is the fastest man in the world Search Relevance Scientist at Yahoo from d2008-04-XX to d2009-12-XX, where Core team member of Yahoo Search Machine Learning ranking team. Designed and implemented large scale machine learning algorithms that made biggest improvements in Yahoo Search Relevance. Associate Research Scientist at Columbia University from d2006-08-XX to d2008-04-XX, where Part of a team that developed a machine learned ranking system to predict potential failures of New York City’s power grid. The prediction was used to prioritize the power grid maintenance and the system was adopted by Con Edison, New York.  Skills include: machine learning, mathematics, web search, economics, teaching, robotics, data mining, distributed computing, software development, programming language, informatics, map reduce, nlp, artificial intelligence, information retrieval, software engineering, pattern recognition, text mining, scalability, algorithms, big data, Python, C++, Natural Language Processing, Distributed Systems, Computer Science, Search Engine, MapReduce.
